25
00:01:22,608 --> 00:01:24,627
Now let's look at Key Takeaways.

26
00:01:24,627 --> 00:01:30,336
Use nouns, not verbs in URLs - let HTTP methods convey the action.

27
00:01:30,336 --> 00:01:34,326
Be consistent with naming, casing, and response formats.

28
00:01:34,326 --> 00:01:38,377
Use proper status codes - they communicate intent clearly.

29
00:01:38,377 --> 00:01:42,632
Implement pagination - never return unbounded lists.

30
00:01:42,632 --> 00:01:46,057
Version your API - breaking changes will happen.

31
00:01:46,057 --> 00:01:51,141
Document thoroughly - OpenAPI/Swagger is your friend.

32
00:01:51,141 --> 00:01:55,168
Handle errors gracefully - descriptive errors help debugging.

33
00:01:55,168 --> 00:02:00,432
Secure by default - authentication, rate limiting, input validation.

34
00:02:00,432 --> 00:02:02,151
Now, let's talk about Conclusion.

35
00:02:02,151 --> 00:02:06,887
Great API design is about empathy for the developers who will use it.

36
00:02:06,887 --> 00:02:12,716
Follow conventions, be consistent, document well, and handle edge cases gracefully.

37
00:02:12,716 --> 00:02:16,838
Your future self (and your API consumers) will thank you.

